==English==
===Etymology===
*''Pangasinan'' (from Pangasinan:  "place of salt" or "place of salt-making") and derived from root word ''asin'' (from Pangasinan: "salt").
*''pangasinan'' (from Pangasinan:  "container of salt or salted-products") and derived from root word ''asin'' (from Pangasinan:  "salt").

===Pronunciation===
* pang-guh-see-nan
* pan-guh-see-nan
* pa-nga-see-nan

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Pangasinan'''
# a [[province]] of the [[Philippines]] located on the west coast of the island of [[Luzon]] along [[Lingayen Gulf]] and [[South China Sea]]
# a [[language]] of the [[Malayo-Polynesian]] branch of the [[Austronesian]] family of languages spoken in the [[Philippines]]; it is the primary language in the province or region of [[Pangasinan]]
# the coastal area of Pangasinan on the west coast of the island of Luzon along [[Lingayen Gulf]] and [[South China Sea]], which is known for its [[salt-making]] industry
# the region of the [[Philippines]] located on the west coast of the island of [[Luzon]] along [[Lingayen Gulf]] and [[South China Sea]] with its distinct [[Pangasinan language]], culture and heritage
# the [[nation]] of Pangasinan
# the [[people]] of Pangasinan
# an [[indigenous speaker]] of the [[Pangasinan language]]
# a [[resident]] or [[inhabitant]] of the province, region or nation of [[Pangasinan]]
# a [[Filipino]] or people from the [[Philippines]]
# a ceramic jar or container for storage of [[salt]] or salted-products
===Adjective===
'''Pangasinan'''
# Of or pertaining to the Pangasinan language
# Of or pertaining to the Pangasinan people
# Of or pertaining to the Pangasinan province, region or nation
# Of or pertaining to the process of salt-making, and the use and storage of salt or salted-products
# Of or pertaining to the Pangasinan coastal area known for its salt-making industry

